# Testing your in-person verifier with the GOV.UK Wallet Sandbox

The GOV.UK Wallet Sandbox will let you create a test driving licence and save it to the GOV.UK Wallet test app. You can then present the test driving licence to your verification service and confirm your service is able to [receive credential information](/consuming-and-verifying-credentials). You will be able to complete this flow on Android and iOS devices.

The GOV.UK Wallet sandbox will contain:

- a [document builder](), which lets you issue test digital driving licences
- a test app, which lets you store and share a test digital driving licence
- a [mock status list service](), which lets you revoke or check the status of your test driving licence
- the certificate authority, which manages the certificates you need to connect to GOV.UK Wallet

The GOV.UK Wallet Sandbox tools are for testing and development only. You must not use the tools in your production environment or as part or your live deployment process. The sandbox is limited to testing the Verifiable Presentation of a credential.

## Before you use the GOV.UK Wallet Sandbox

To use the GOV.UK Wallet Sandbox, you must:

- be a certified Digital Verification Services (DVS) provider on the [digital identity and attribute services register](https://www.digital-identity-services-register.service.gov.uk/)
- complete the enrollment process for a DVS
- have been given access to verifier test tools (for example, TestFlight or Google Play Console) and installed these on your device
- have received an integration certificate from us

If you have not completed these steps, speak to your GOV.UK Wallet engagement manager or [contact us](/contact-us).

## Using the GOV.UK Wallet Sandbox document builder

You can use the [document builder](https://stub-credential-issuer.wallet-onboarding.integration.account.gov.uk/dvs/start) to:

- [issue a new test digital driving licence]()
- [revoke an issued test digital driving licence]()

You should use the test licence to test the end-to-end journey of your verification service.

### Issue a test driving licence

1. Access the [sandbox document builder](https://stub-credential-issuer.wallet-onboarding.integration.account.gov.uk/dvs/start) to begin issuing a test driving licence. 

1. Click "Start now".

1. Choose "Issue a new test digital driving licence" and click Continue.  

 The document builder will issue a new test driving licence for you to use. The test driving licence will have:

- a unique driving licence number in the format `Test-{TIMESTAMP}`
- a credential issuer of "GDS Verifier Integration"

You should add the test driving licence to your GOV.UK Wallet test app, and use the licence to test your verification service.

### Revoke a test credential

Credential issuers can [revoke a credential](/status-list/revoke-credential/) they have issued. Your verification service must recognise when a credential has been revoked by the issuer and must cancel the verification flow.

The document builder allows you to revoke [test credentials you have previously issued](#issue-a-test-credential).

To revoke a test credential:

1. Make a note of the test driving licence number you want to revoke. 

1. Access the [sandbox document builder](https://stub-credential-issuer.wallet-onboarding.integration.account.gov.uk/dvs/start).  

1. Choose "Revoke an issued test digital driving licence" and click Continue.

1. Enter the test driving licence number you want to revoke. 

<%= warning_text('You cannot reissue a test driving licence that has been revoked. Make sure you have the correct licence number before you click Continue. If you revoke a test driving licence incorrectly, you must use the document builder to issue a new one.') %>

GOV.UK Wallet checks the status of credentials in the app when it is opened, and will invalidate your revoked driving licence. Before you test your revoked credential flow, you should set the device with your GOV.UK Wallet test app to airplane mode. If GOV.UK Wallet invalidates the licence you should issue and revoke a new one. 

## Using the sandbox mock status list

Credential issuers can use the [status list service](/status-list/) to [check a credential's status](status-list/statuslist/#check-a-credential-39-s-status). When you are testing your verification service, you must use the mock status list to check the status of your test driving licence.

### Check the status of a test driving licence

You can check the status of a [test driving licence you have issued](#issue-a-test-credential) with the following urls:

- https://status-list-mock.mobile.integration.account.gov.uk/.well-known/jwks.json
- https://status-list-mock.mobile.integration.account.gov.uk/t/`{STATUS_LIST_IDENTIFIER}` 

The value of `STATUS_LIST_IDENTIFIER` will be unique to your test credential.

The urls for the mock status list are different to those in production.  You must not use live credential status information for your testing environment.

### Understand the capabilities of the mock status list

The mock status list has a limited functionality compared to the live status list service. You should understand these differences and consider them in your testing.

The mock status list will:

- issue access tokens with a longer validity than the status list service
- have fewer status options than the status list service
- set the value of the `exp` claim to the expiry of the credential plus 30 days
- set the `ttl` claim to a short value

There is more information available about the [`exp` and `ttl` claims](status-list/statuslist/#token-status-list-request-example-request-response-payload).




